          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Pu-240, Pu-241, Pu-242 targets were used. The targets",
                "were prepared by the molecular plating method. The",
                "targets material was placed onto 200 mug/cm**2 Ni foils",
                "with supporting Cu backing. Target thicknesses were in",
                "most cases determinate from the alpha-counting, using",
                "a surface -barrier silicon detector. The",
                "electrodeposited targets were typically of thickness",
                "100-400 mug/cm**2.",
                "The isotopic composition of the target material, based",
                "on the specification of the supplier, AERE, Harwell",
                "and in parentheses( performed in Belgium),",
                "corrected for decay of Pu-241 into Am-241 is given.",
                "Pu-240-98.0(98.9)%, Pu-239 1.91(0.95%),Pu-241+Am-241",
                "0.074(0.060)%, Pu-242 0.019(0.051)%,",
                "Pu-241-78.8+16.1(normalized to 78.8%),Pu-239 1.5(1.6)%,",
                "Pu-240 3.09(3.14)%, Pu-242 0.49(0.50)%,",
                "Pu-242-90.88(92.13), Pu-239 3.13(3.03)%, Pu-240 2.90",
                " (2.29)%, Pu-241+Am-241 3.09(2.54)%"
              ]
            }
          ],
